+# 🤖 OmniRoute - AI API Gateway & Router
+
+OmniRoute is an intelligent API gateway that routes requests to various AI language models (LLMs) with advanced optimization capabilities. It provides token compression, automatic fallback mechanisms, multimodal API support, and comprehensive caching strategies to reduce costs while improving response quality.
+
+## 📋 Stack Overview
+
+This template deploys **OmniRoute** with all essential components:
+
+- **OmniRoute Service** - The main AI gateway/router application
+- **Redis Cache** - In-memory data store for caching, sessions, and state management
+- **Persistent Storage** - Dedicated volumes for application data and cache persistence
+
+## 🎯 Key Features
+
+- **Token Compression** - RTK + Caveman stack compression saves 15-95% tokens
+- **Smart Auto-Fallback** - Automatic fallback between multiple AI providers
+- **Multi-Modal Support** - Handles various API types including MCP (Model Context Protocol) and A2A (Agent-to-Agent)
+- **Multiple Interface Options** - Desktop app and Progressive Web App (PWA) support
+- **Semantic Caching** - Reduces redundant API calls with intelligent caching
+- **Low-Resource Optimization** - Designed to run on VPS with <1GB RAM
+- **Security First** - Built-in JWT authentication, API key management, and secure storage encryption
+
+## 🚀 Quick Start
+
+### Prerequisites
+
+- Docker and Docker Compose installed
+- Coolify instance (for simplified deployment) or Docker environment
+- Minimum 1GB RAM available
+- Basic understanding of environment variables
+
+### Deployment Steps
+
+1. **Deploy the Template**
+   - In Coolify, select this template during the service creation
+   - Or use `docker compose up -d` in the template directory
+
+2. **Initial Configuration**
+   - The application generates security credentials automatically via Coolify
+   - Administrator password is set via `SERVICE_PASSWORD_ADMIN`
+   - Access the dashboard at the configured domain
+
+3. **Configure API Providers**
+   - Add your AI provider API keys in the OmniRoute dashboard
+   - Set up routing rules for different use cases
+   - Configure fallback chains for reliability
+
+## ⚙️ Configuration
+
+### Required Environment Variables
+
+These variables are automatically handled by Coolify:
+
+```
+SERVICE_URL_OMNIROUTE_20128      # Dashboard URL (auto-generated by Coolify)
+SERVICE_URL_OMNIROUTE_20129      # API endpoint URL (auto-generated by Coolify)
+SERVICE_PASSWORD_ADMIN           # Initial admin password (set in Coolify)
+SERVICE_BASE64_JWT               # JWT secret (auto-generated)
+SERVICE_BASE64_API               # API key secret (auto-generated)
+SERVICE_BASE64_STORAGE           # Storage encryption key (auto-generated)
+```
+
+### Key Application Variables
+
+| Variable | Default | Purpose |
+|----------|---------|---------|
+| `NODE_ENV` | `production` | Node.js environment mode |
+| `PORT` | `20128` | Dashboard and main service port |
+| `API_PORT` | `20129` | API server port |
+| `OMNIROUTE_MEMORY_MB` | `256` | Memory limit for OmniRoute process (MB) |
+| `REDIS_URL` | `redis://redis:6379` | Redis connection string |
+| `NODE_OPTIONS` | `--dns-result-order=ipv4first` | Fixes DNS issues on dual-stack VPS |
+
+### Optional Tuning Variables
+
+```
+APP_LOG_LEVEL=warn              # Logging level (debug, info, warn, error)
+APP_LOG_TO_FILE=false           # Enable file-based logging
+PROMPT_CACHE_MAX_BYTES=1048576  # Max prompt cache size (1MB)
+SEMANTIC_CACHE_MAX_BYTES=2097152 # Max semantic cache size (2MB)
+```
+
+### Resource Limits
+
+- **OmniRoute Container**: 512MB RAM (adjustable via `mem_limit`)
+- **Redis Container**: 128MB RAM (adjustable via `mem_limit`)
+- **Designed for**: <1GB total VPS environments
+
+## 📊 Ports
+
+- **20128** - Dashboard UI and main web interface
+- **20129** - API server for programmatic access
+
+Access these via your configured domain in Coolify.
+
+## 💾 Data Persistence
+
+Two named volumes are created:
+
+- `omniroute-prod-data` - Application data, configurations, and user settings
+- `omniroute-redis-data` - Redis cache and session data
+
+Data is automatically backed up every 60 seconds by Redis persistence settings.
+
+## 🔐 Security Considerations
+
+1. **Automatic Secret Generation** - All secrets are auto-generated by Coolify
+2. **Secure Cookies** - `AUTH_COOKIE_SECURE=true` enforces HTTPS
+3. **Storage Encryption** - Data encryption via `STORAGE_ENCRYPTION_KEY`
+4. **Memory Limits** - Prevents resource exhaustion attacks
+5. **Health Checks** - Continuous service monitoring and auto-restart
+
+## 🛠️ Troubleshooting
+
+### Issue: Service fails to start
+- **Check memory**: Ensure sufficient RAM available
+- **DNS issues**: Already handled with `NODE_OPTIONS=--dns-result-order=ipv4first`
+- **Redis connection**: Verify Redis container is healthy with `docker ps`
+
+### Issue: High memory usage
+- Reduce `PROMPT_CACHE_MAX_BYTES` or `SEMANTIC_CACHE_MAX_BYTES`
+- Decrease `OMNIROUTE_MEMORY_MB` if safe
+- Monitor with `docker stats`
+
+### Issue: Slow API responses
+- Check Redis container health
+- Review log level (`APP_LOG_LEVEL`) for diagnostic info
+- Verify network connectivity to AI providers
+
+### Issue: Dashboard not loading
+- Verify port 20128 is accessible
+- Check if domain is correctly configured in Coolify
+- Review browser console for errors
+
+### View Logs
+
+```bash
+# OmniRoute logs
+docker logs <omniroute-container-id>
+
+# Redis logs
+docker logs <redis-container-id>
+
+# Real-time monitoring
+docker compose logs -f
+```
+
+## 📚 Additional Resources
+
+- **OmniRoute Project**: https://github.com/diegosouzapw/omniroute
+- **Docker Documentation**: https://docs.docker.com/
+- **Redis Documentation**: https://redis.io/docs/
+- **Node.js Best Practices**: https://nodejs.org/en/docs/
+
+## 🎓 Complexity Level
+
+🟡 **Intermediate**
+
+- Multiple interconnected services (OmniRoute + Redis)
+- Moderate configuration with 20+ environment variables
+- Requires understanding of API routing and caching concepts
+- Estimated setup time: 10-15 minutes including provider configuration
+
+## 📝 Notes
+
+- This template is optimized for resource-constrained environments
+- Redis persistence is configured with 60-second intervals (balance between safety and performance)
+- The application includes built-in healthchecks for automatic recovery
+- Suitable for production deployments with proper backup strategies
